Add (as shown in in the current W3C-CSS2-spec, chapter 5.8.1)

  H1[title] { color: blue; }

to a CSS stylesheet to be parsed, and the parser will fail around line 660 in 
org/apache/batik/css/parser/Parser.java ("key { expected "); my version of 
Parser.java with this issue is "Parser.java,v 1.7 2001/01/18 19:42:25 hillion 
Exp $". The bug can be resolved by modifying 
org.apache.batik.css.parser.Parser.parseSimpleSelector(), line 764 as follows:

    case LexicalUnits.LEFT_BRACKET:
        if (nextIgnoreSpaces() != LexicalUnits.IDENTIFIER) {
            throw createCSSParseException("identifier");
        }
        String name = scanner.currentValue();
        int op = nextIgnoreSpaces();
        switch (op) {
        case LexicalUnits.RIGHT_BRACKET:    // bugfix
            nextIgnoreSpaces();             // bugfix
        default:
            c = conditionFactory.createAttributeCondition(name, null, false,
                                                          null);
            break;

A rebuild via "build.bat dist-zip" produced (among other things) a healed 
version of batik-css.jar which does not show this bug. Please give me a short 
notice in case this bugfix cannot be validated.

Best regards,

Michael Hartle
